  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add onion, carrot, celery and sauté until the vegetables soften, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add tomato paste, dried thyme, smoked paprika, salt and pepper; cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in marsala wine, let it reduce for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.",
    "Add lentils and stir to coat them in the aromatics.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes until lentils are tender.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed, then serve hot.",
    "Sprinkle fresh herbs or a squeeze of lemon if desired before serving."
